caption: Loved the backyard garden area for dinner. Open kitchen you get to walk through and they had wood burning stove that provided a great outdoors scent.  A lot of mezcal options and different mole options.  Right now it is a pre-fix menu but each course has a lot of great options.  On the entrees we really enjoyed the trout, and for other courses the scallops (like a spicy ceviche) and the venison.  If you want a sweet dessert get the churros. The mole cake and then the apple and ice cream desert were almost more savory than sweet. Still tasted great

The four course dinner was truly delicious and beautifully presented. The octopus starter, and beef tacos were some of the highlights. Seating out in the back patio had a nice ambience and there were heated lamps. All cocktails are mezcal based though, but there is a wine and beer list.

This restaurant had been on my wishlist for a long time and finally I tried it! Amazing! No doubt, one of my favorite mexican in the city. Highly recommend their tostada, the octopus is soooooo good! Will definitely come back!

We went for the three course Sunday brunch and start to finish the meal was so delicious and the food was beautiful!! Their outdoor patio space is large and nicely decorated.  The service was exceptional and the margaritas were 💯! It was the perfect way to kick of spring with friends and I look forward to going back soon. 10/10 recommend!
Best Mexican place ever Chef and team created a unique experience Oaxaca all day. Food, agave, art and a great space in the back yard!

Wonderful experience dining at Claro. Highly polished Oaxacan cuisine. I had the 4-course dinner in the outdoor seating. The restaurant’s menu is exotic and I’m very pleased with the vegetarian options offered. Claro is a great choice for a date or another special occasion in your life.

Claro is unreal.  The food is so delicious and interesting, and i've never had a single thing on the menu i didn't enjoy.  we use this as our special occasion spot because there are delicious cocktails and the service is incredible.  it's got a really nice laidback vibe while still being food of Michelin caliber.  i *CRAVE* the tortillas for days after. the enchiladas are so fresh and delicious, and the aguachile is next level. it's a must-visit if you're in Brooklyn and looking for an outstanding meal.

First time coming here.  Went with the 4 course diner special, amazing from beginning to end.  Had a total of 2 drinks and each was as fantastic as the food.  The staff was amazing and very attentive.  Will be visiting this location again in the future.
Great food and great drinks with a great atmosphere. Would highly recommend
The food here is freaking amazing. Best Mexican food in the city hands down. I do recommend you go check them out for yourself.
Excellent food and service.  They have good outdoor heated space.
Excellent food, excellent drinks, excellent service, excellent attention to COVID protocols.

Visiting from Texas and truly enjoyed dining at Claro this past weekend. Following all CDC guidelines and rules, Claro provided our table of 4 a delicious four-course meal and of course, a mezcal flight.  Their staff works together hand in hand and ensured they met any dietary restrictions if needed. Their bar manager was fully knowledgeable on having provided us detailed information on their extensive mezcal list.
Customer service is on point here, they're quick to come out and greet you as soon as you walk up.

Claro has one of the best set ups by virtue of the garden in back. The Oaxacan cuisine allows you and your taste buds to day dream of sunny days and salsa infused nights in a very different climate. I had the Mexican hot chocolate which compliments the huilacoche empanada better than one would expect. Obviously the barbacoa tacos are a must, and trust me, you want to stick around for dessert!
We did the 4 course menue. Mole was the star and is a must, octopus tacos was delicious. Highly recommend for nyc dining. And toasty outdoor heaters.
Fantastic food, amazing service, great cocktails
Delicious!

Fantastic menu that’s a real treat to explore. They have done a great job balancing all of these interesting flavors and making great shareable dishes. The cocktails are very tasty. Recommended if you’re looking for a fancier lunch. The staff are attentive and kind

Amazing food. Been here twice (once before COVID and one during COVID) and each time the dishes have been spectacular. You really can't go wrong with anything, but if you can, save room for the chocolate mole cake for dessert!
Deliciousness!
Some of the best mole in NYC
I visit this place a lot since I work nearby. I got to say the service is always excellent and they keep the place well organized regularly. Rates are affordable and they serve large portions.
Beautiful outdoor space with great service.
Both dinner and brunch menus are flavorful and unforgettable. Clean, safe and professional. Server was able to easily help me navigate menu with pregnancy dietary restrictions. Patio is gorgeous.

The mole lava cake is one of those desserts that I cannot stop thinking about it. I really enjoyed the whole menu, one of the best brunches that I've had in the city if I'm thinking about price, originality and quality. Although, the hot chocolate isn't worth it for the size.
Outstanding refined Mexican cuisine with a nice back garden.  Great mole, astonishing mezcal selection and overall great

This place is amazing. We came for dinner & sat in the back patio. Very nice ambiance! We each had a choice of 4 dishes from each course. Very well thought out dishes! It is definitely more than enough food! They also offer Mezcal flights! probably my favorite part. The Claro team curated the entire dinner perfectly so that you aren’t stacked with multiple plates at a time & each dish comes out fresh. Wonderful service with how busy it got back there! I enjoyed it so much I only had time for one photo: Tostada de Pulpo.
Went for the brunch menu and it did not disappoint. So happy I took my girlfriend here was a great start to our day

I’ve had prior good meals here but had brunch here a few weekends ago. It was a prix fixe for $45 per person. Most dishes good but my masa pancakes were undercooked and partially raw and gooey inside. I would have expected much better from a Michelin starred restaurant.
Phenomenal! Super friendly and attentive staff, and delicious food. Well balanced textures and flavors. Short ribs on the brunch menu are heavy and could use something acidic.
Really delicious regional food served in Covid-responsible way
Where can I even begin, the flavors are amazing. This is a must have.

One Michelin star, please keep it! Elevated, a bit experimental Mexican cuisine with an impressive mezcal list. Charming terrace. Fun idea: order mezcals and try to smell the infused aromas ranging from mango to chicken! Yes, I said chicken.

Absolutely fantastic meal. The tortillas and tostadas unlike any I have had in NYC, a robust flavor anchor, not just texture and structure. The proteins were very good, but the vegetable components really the star of each dish. Cocktails creative and complementary to the food, and exceptionally well executed. Get the mezcal ice cream to finish. Looking forward to our return.

Excellent food and great atmosphere in the vine-shaded outdoor patio. The waiter graciously walked us through the dinner menu and made excellent suggestions based on our individual taste preferences. We ordered off the tasting menu and loved everything, especially the Mole Rojo and mole chocolate cake dessert.
Some excellent food, lovely patio space out back, and good service.

Having heard about Claro for so long, my expectations were pretty high. But from beginning to end, it was an incredible experience - food, drink and service  (definitely try a personalized mezcal flight as a digestif) it was the first meal I’ve had this year that truly made me miss pre-covid nyc and everything the city can be. Can’t recommend highly enough.

Must have been an off day for the chef. Ordered the lamb chops medium. Was clearly lamb loin that arrived in my plate with a heart beat.  Second time it arrived it was still kicking and had a very gamy smell. Server had a bit of an attitude as well, or perhaps just the language barrier. Not really sure. Would not make the trek to this place again.
Fantastic backyard setting. Delicious drinks and divine food. Great service too! Worth the splurge.

Great service, excellent menu. Fantastic four course set menu right now at really reasonable price. Fried oyster tostada, duck and magnificent churros. Great share night and family night if you get first sitting. Already booked to go back.
This place is extraordinary.
Best beef
Great tasting menu and the Italian white wine was fantastic. Mole Rojo was amazing. The two flights of mezcal we ordered were en fuego 🔥.
A spectacular gem of a restaurant that has managed to create a romantic environment despite the insane circumstances. Felt like a break from reality. And the food! I mean c’mon.
We came for a brunch and had a fixed 3 courses menu. Excellent cuisine and service. The outdoor pergola vine patio is fresh and charming.
Excellent brunch food and nice dessert!

I almost cried the first time I ate here from how good the food was. Go in the summer. The plant-based dishes will blow you away.  Their meat dishes are excellent, but what really shines is their produce dishes.  The tomato and goat cheese salad. I’ve never had a better experience with tomatoes in my life. Don’t understand how it’s so good. The pea and avocado tostadas are so, so good as well.  My husband and I went for weekend brunch again recently (limited tasting menu during COVID). Had an amazing experience! Their backyard space is lovely. The food was excellent as always, and we really enjoyed their frozen cocktails as well.
The food was delicious. I loved the ensalada and the Tacos de Camaron. The service was great as well. Definitely would recommend.
Great backyard

The food was ok. The red mole was really good.  I’m used to being really impressed. I was very happy that they were open for business sustaining themselves through this tough time so KUDOS to Claro. Thankful to have been there for an infrequent evening out.
I am Mexican. This restaurant blew my mind. The michelada is one of the best I’ve had. their patio is a great escape.
delicious food, awesome service and an amazing mezcal collection. Bravo!  best molote ever. with mint 🤯

Everything was delicious here!! Small plates but lots a flavor in each dish. We had the tacos de tinga, quesadilla, the pork rib tacos and a few others. All excellent choices. For a party of 4, we ordered 7-9 dishes and it was sufficient.
Good flavours, tasty drinks but for whatever reason the restaurant thinks that it’s necessary to deafen patrons with (far too loud, if catchy) 90s pop hits.
Reasonable price for its fun but classy atmosphere, the tacos were very tasty. I was left wanting a bit of something more but it was still solid. Check it out if you’re in the area
Some of the best upscale Mexican food I've had. The beet tostada was out of this world and the whole place had a polished yet friendly/local Vibe. Easy food to share also!
One of my favorite Mexican spots, perfect for date night. Everything we’ve had is delicious and their cocktails and fantastic as well! Looking forward to dining in the backyard in the summer.
Outstanding in every way. Great scene and vibe; amazing tacos and tostados; best mezcal list In Brooklyn.
Fun place to grab a cocktail or a bite.  The mushroom (pizza, for lack of a better word) dish was highlight of my meal.  Vegetarian friendly!
Great service, awesome vibe, great selection of cocktails and mezcal  😍
Great food...Excellent service...The Yellowfin Tostada was wonderful. The Maria Sabina Memela was a pleasant surprise which I also recommend. Overall nice experience.
Really incredible experience !
Aaaaaaaaaaaa-mazing!
Food is good 😋😋 and the staff here is very friendly 👍

Completely gluten-free menu! But don’t let that deter you non-celiacars out there. Dishes are whole foods (very little processed foods) and are carried by rice or corn products. And the mezcal! An impressive array of types. This is the place to go if you like sipping your mezcal neat with sal de gusano dusted orange slices. Was missing the capulines but I understand, it’s a niche market. There are also a number of impressive mezcal based mixed drinks, I went ahead and got a mezcal flight. Knowledgeable and friendly staff. Cool place. GF friendly. Easy to citibike to. I sat at the bar but you should probably make a reservation if you go with three or more people. I’ll definitely be back.

I don't know if the chef was off today, but none of the four dishes we had could be described as delicious. Camarones, tuna, pork ribs, and pork cheek. All over-salted and over complicated in a bad way. Reyes Deli is now even higher on my esteem level, given how much better their tacos are than a restaurant with a Michelin star. Bartender was lovely though.
Awesome Tacos and food in geneal... cool atmosphere
Inventive and impeccably prepared Mexican dishes. One of the best meals I've had in some time. First class service as well.
First time at Claro the food was good, but nothing to write home about, but second time we went the food was definitely a level up. We shared 8 dishes and greatly enjoyed them.
Got a spot at the bar. Great service. Great drinks. Phenomenal food. Will definitely be back!

I forget what it was called exactly, but the corn based dish was exquisite. Heed any warnings you are given about spice, some are dishes are non trivial.  Would love to see more non alcoholic drink options on the menu (a beer specifically).
A place is to be missed if you love mezcal and Mexican, or should I say Oaxaca, food. Rather pricey yet not disappointing, Michelin recommended:)

Probably the high-quality Mexican eating place in NYC. Absolutely delicious food and a fab vibe. The liquids are original, with such specific touches as avocado salt on margarita rims  instead of normal salt. On the pricier side but so well worth it.
Very nice cozy place.  The food was exceptional.   Definitely going back.
Have only been here for desserts, but boy, what desserts! Would recommend to anyone in a heartbeat. Friendly staff and incredible food.
They have ded rats under the tables

one of my favorite restaurants in new york!! as someone with celiac, I appreciate the 100% gluten free menu accompanied with the atmosphere of a restaurant that does not advertise itself as such. really tasty, authentic Mexican cuisine and everyone who works there is really nice.
(Translated by Google) Great Mexican food, cozy, not loud, affordable prices for New York  (Original) Ottima cucina messicana, locale accogliente, non rumoroso, prezzi abbordabili per New York
always nice service and food, great outdoor space
The tuna tostada is incredible
The fact that the food is unique and was given a lot of thought doesn't mean that it is good or tasty.

On one of our visits for dinner we had a beautiful salad with a chapulin (grasshopper) vinaigrette and it was so amazing that we ran back 48 hours later only to learn that it's not a regular item on the menu. That said, everything here was terrific and tasty. The handmade tortillas are perfect on their own too. But be prepared, these are small plates. (Muy small.) And they encourage sharing so even smaller. The staff is good about recommendations based on the size of the party and size of the appetites present which is very helpful.

Wish i can say it was great unfortunately,  when we arrived there was no note nor on the door or the website that the restaurant would be closed we traveled from far way being from Oaxaca we were bummed that one of the employees said it was closed and sadly didnt get the opportunity to try the food and called several times no answer  .
Loved everything we ordered. Super delicious food!!!!!
Interesting creative Mexican food. Small menu but everything is done really well. Huge mezcal list and lots of creative drinks.
Great Mexican
Interesting and flavorful Mexican food...great specialty drinks ..a Michelin Star but casual & not too expensive.
Very tasty dishes and drinks
Pricey but great creative modern Mexican food in a small but quaint ambiance.
Flavorful, elevated Mexican with a huge Mezcal selection. Friendly, professional service. Comfortable medium-sized room with good sized bar with multiple solo diners.

There is no question that the kitchen has some flair and imagination. The dishes we had were simple yet distinctive and were presented well. But it comes at a cost. The prices are very high for what is effectively a combination of some  of the cheapest ingredients available in the US. The service is fixed somewhere between pompous and surly. And worst of all it’s clear that some of the waiting staff haven’t been trained well in basic operational functions. My case in point is that when it came to payment, one of the staff tried to input my debit card number many times (incorrectly on each attempt as it happened) and of course my bank immediately contacted me as it assumed it was fraud and blocked my card for two days (this was a sat night and my bank’s fraud team don’t work on Sunday’s). I didn’t receive an apology on the night for the ineptitude nor subsequently for the inconvenience caused. So, taken altogether,  a very mixed bag. I’m giving Claro just one star because they’ve had the opportunity to respond to the two messages I’ve left them earlier this week but they have failed to do so. That speaks volumes to me and is certainly an indication that the issues are more likely to be with the management team rather than the waiting staff themselves. If you’re craving their food - and it is pretty good - then my advice is get it to go. The rest is noise.
Get the mole, you won't regret it
Seasoning of the food is excellent. Will definitely be back.... Wait staff very helpful.
Really great food. All the tacos were amazing. Octopus was spectacular. Service was fantastic , and the waiter was knowledgeable. Be sure to get the black beans!
Mezcal holy grail
Food is so heavy and chicharrón is not real chicharrón! It’s like to order potatoes and they give you potatoes chips!

I was on a fact finding tour for a new bar in Belfast. New York and Oaxaca, the destinations. I found a little Oaxacan gem in Brooklyn, with two biblical hosts, Noah and Adam. There was a Keanu Reeves passing by out front, but the star of the show was a Rabbit mole and a mezcal cocktail, and the two hosts. Thanks boys. Epic!
Great food small dishes. Still way worth it.

The food was delicious but a bit heavy. Everything was so good, but my the second course I was way too full. Perhaps smaller portions or lighter sauces would help? Service and ambiance were wonderful. I’d go back.
BUT

Came for brunch. Great decor inside and nice outside patio. Delicious drinks. Very expensive small plates ($20 for a quesadilla with 2 corn tortillas). Service was a bit pushy and not very friendly. Not a very authentic experience but a trendy place with unique dishes.
One star Michelin Mexican. You can't go wrong. And a lot of mezcal to go with it...
The mole is amazing

Amazingly authentic Oaxacan food. I’ve had everything on the menu and they haven’t missed on any. Pricey? Maybe, but you get what you pay for. If you want a cheap place to grab a taco you’ll find plenty of amazing places in Sunset Park. But, if you want mind-glowingly good Mexican cuisine you won’t find a better place in NYC.

In rating Claro, I wavered between giving it three and four stars. In some sense, my giving any "star" rating is a bit misleading here, because the evening was so mixed. The food was actually very good, among the best Mexican food that I have had here in New York City. On the other hand, the air-conditioning, on an exceptionally hot day, was either not working or not on at all, so the place replicated Mexico in more ways than one. Further, while the service was polite and friendly, it was also a mess, with two different dishes missing (our dinner companions noted that they had had the same experience the last time they were there). Finally, given the prices, I would expect more of a complete dining experience from a restaurant. This was easily the most expensive Mexican restaurant that I have ever eaten at. Hence, my decision to give it three stars despite the excellent food.
Such an amazing experience.decided to go for brunch with a friend.Everything was delicious and beautifully presented.definitely want to go back to try the dinner menu.
Super tasty! Service a bit chaotic, I forgive them!
Amazing food..unique offerings!
Fantastic Mexican food. Great backyard--eat out there if you can
Always delicious.
So amazing. Food, cocktails staff are all wonderful
Creative menu, very tight space so reservations are a must.

Excellent tostadas piled high with creative fresh ingredients....octopus/bacon...tuna/orange...Turkey tacos with blue cheese...they also grilled up some basic quesadillas for our kids on their housemade corn tortillas
I had one of the best meals I have ever had in my life here.
Best Mexican in Brooklyn

I live at the uptown end of the A train in Inwood and I'd make the treck to Claro anytime! It was my first visit and will not be the last. The mezcal selection was impressive and the lengua tacos were deliciously crispy. The mole wasn't what I expected based on reviews but the short rib was cooked well. I'll have to come back when barbacoa is back on the menu.
Very limited menu
Awesome brunch

This place was fantastic. The staff seated us quite late in the evening but that didn't stop them from taking care of us. The hospitality was amazing and the food on point. As Londoners we don't always get to treat ourselves to good Mexican food and this place didn't disappoint. Also the homage to Maria Sabina was great 😁

Having just visited Oaxaca city every bite felt like we were back in Mexico. The Black Mole Beef was out of this world, that was our main course. We had two apps, both hearty and delicious and 4 cocktails between us because they were too good!

Eclectic Mexican.  Not sure how else to explain this.  If you want great Mexican food this probably isn't it.   The dishes (limited menu) has Mexican an themed dishes but you won't find things like Nachos, burritos or any traditional dishes.
Great creative food and excellent mezcal selection

I was so impressed by the food and the aesthetic - dishes came out beautifully and lived up to all expectations. The flavor was so clean in each dish, with contrast and clarity - I loved this meal so, so much.

AN EYE OPENER for anyone new to the varieties of cookery, spicing and pairings under the sweeping term, Mexican food.  The venue and furnishings at Claro are plain, sited by an old-school Italian social club, but the dishes are distinctive and dazzle. Try several with mole, a specialty of Oaxaca, the restaurant’s lodestar in the kitchen. Cocktails at Claro with mezcal are cool and also a specialty of Oaxaca.  Competition for reservations at the place is a blood sport.

Found! Incredible Oaxaca cuisine, truly memorable. The restaurant is dedicated to making everything in-house and using locally sourced, non-GMO ingredients. This care is evident in the delicious cuisine! The tortillas are wood fired and pressed to perfection. The mole is outstanding. The vibe is cool, especially the backyard if you are there on a nice day/night. Excellent tequila selections as well! For more great finds visit TheLoupe!
The chilaquiles were the best! The only disappointment was that I ordered a dish with chicharrón but instead received pork rinds in the dish.

Omfg. Everything I've eaten here is delectable. Perfect shares. Brilliantly spicy. Pair with mezcal for every meal. Seriously. They have a great selection of mezcal. I hate mezcal but I will drink it (and enjoy it) here. If you're thinking about exploring the agave liquor, this is the spot. Go for a late lunch on the weekend, get a spot in the backyard, and order the mezcal flight with their fish dish.
Great food.  Small portions.  Friendly service, but for a reservation book one month ahead or you can eat at the counter
Finally, we got to go to this wonderful place! Great food, great mezcal, not cheap! Will definitely go again! Nettles and queso empenada-- fantastic.
I was skeptical about paying $6 for a taco ($18 for 3) - it was out of this world. This place is friggin delicious.
This is a $$$$ restaurant with $ quality. 3 super small tacos for $19 ! Not even a side Tongue tacos are the worst I ever had . Fatty pieces of tongue Avoid
From the bartender curating a mezcal flight based on my tastes to 4 courses of arguably the best Mexican cuisine we've ever had, Claro is absolutely a must-try.
OMG this is the best Mexican food; lived in Tucson, but this place is so special. Fantastic service , food, and gracious people.
Flavors like a Top 40 production, in a good way.
So good... just go and enjoy (not for vegetarians)
Fantastic. Pure craft every step of the way.

Wow. Presented in a simple manor, the complexity and preparation going into each dish is extraordinary. The cocktails are all equally as interesting. Don't think about what your eating and make sure you end the night with a mezcal shooter out of the empty bone marrow dish.

After an extensive Google search of Mexican spots, I stumbled on Claro. It's a trendy place to get eclectic cocktails and carefully prepared dishes. The service was excellent. Jose the bartender took the time to elaborate on the menu. I had a drink called.... Ugh, I forget; it's first on the list. The vibe is chill, however, a bit bright for dinner.  The place is a bit pricey but worth every penny. It's a good place to discover mezcal as well. I look forward to going back. Oh and the chocolate cake 🎂 🍫 was great, they also have a rice pudding that I'll comment later on.
WOW! Bartender was fantastic. Food was great. Staff was educated. Reservations are a must. Really nice vibe.  Could use more space between tables though.
NYC needs more Mexican food like this. Order anything seafood...
I've been here a couple of times. The food is inventive, but not really special. And it's too spicy. Also, frankly, it's too expensive for what it is. Nah.
The food is definitely good but not Michelin star. Everyone who works there has a ton of attitude. Come on people - chill out. This is BK.
Every table around us ordered the yellowfin tostata and mole dishes. Crowd-pleasers for sure. Go off-scriot and you will be equally rewarded.

Even just based on brunch, one of the best restaurants I’ve been to in a while. Great food- creative without being overly complicated or contrived. The drinks were solid too. The mezcal list is fairly extensive. The plating was well done. The server was attentive and very friendly.

Such a great restaurant. Perfect space in Bk that has housed other great restaurants. This one has artisanal craft in spades. Great mezcal selection. My only gripe is something many might disagree with. Portion size has increased and tostadas are no longer snackable. I just doubled up on my campechao tacos and La Locura mezcal tho so maybe don’t listen to me. LOVE CLARO. BE BACK TOMORROW

If you don’t get the shrimp tacos here you are seriously missing out. The pork rib dish was also amazing! Service was good and fast, was able to make a reservation. Cocktails are good but stay away from the milk punch... it’s extremely sweet. If you love Mexican food, make this a must do!
Was ok. Cocktail spicy and too sweet. You taste everything but mezcal. Tostada( octopus) chewy but maiz azul tostada really fantastic. Staff very friendly.

An instant favorite because of great flavors and original yet recognizable Mexican combinations. The food is served family style as it's prepared and it's perfect to share. The tongue and sweetbreads tacos were our favorite because of texture and rich flavor, and while juicy they didn't feel greasy. The mole rojo was delicious, especially the tender meat. The mushroom wild memela was tasty, but not as complex. They only had one dessert option, chocolate mole cake, but in contrast to the food, it was dry and the flavors were flat.  One major annoyance was the bar seating: space is tight and the waiters kept bumping into our chairs; also the floor boards were loose, so whenever someone walked behind us, our chair would rattle.

Was not at all impressed by the food in this restaurant. Perhaps it's an acquired taste?  I though that beef cheek was overcooked to a gelatinous state and had no texture. I also expected that tacos will have marriage of textures, something crunchy, something creamy and some cilantro would have helped as it was too boring. Slaw was incredibly acidic and salty, perhaps it's the recipe calls for that much vinegar or lime, but we could not eat it. And the amount of onions was overwhelming.  We saw people at the next tables loving every bite, as I said it was not to our taste.
Really fantastic food, but don't let the Michelin star expectations set your standards too high. The molé alone is worth stopping in for.
Mexican inspired spot with a hip vibe. The selection of mezcal is infinite and well supplied. Definitely will come back.
Food was delicious,  meat perfectly cooked. Wonderful blend of smoke and heat,  even the sides could stand by themselves. Can't wait to come back.

The food here is great. I've come a couple times and always enjoy what I order. It's very interesting and tastes great.  The service is rude. They recently got a Michelin star. In my opinion this is rediculous. Michelin needs to relax and travel to some other places and give credit where it's due. The bartenders here are rude. The waiters are pretentious and not friendly. The food is very very good. Not amazing. I travel constantly and love going out to eat. I've eaten at several starred restaurants in the world and this place doesn't belong anywhere near the club. Keep working on your menu and get your attitude together Claro. You really aren't as cool as you think you are.
As close to this part of Mexico as you will get to. Very highly recommended!

Good ingredients resulting in good food, but some plates are more adventurous than others. As long as you don't let the Michelin star set your expectations too high, you will be very happy. The bar is limited to mezcal-type cocktails including an interesting "oscuro" drink that includes absinthe and lemon zest.
Delicious Mexican cuisine. We had ordered 4 dishes between the 2 of us and everything tasted great. Two of them were vegetarian dishes. I also got mezcal based negroni - that was good too
Outstanding savory dishes, and good friendly service, but was served an inedible dessert, then was comped a not very good other dessert.

Good seasonal modern Mexican but I think because of all the hype I was expecting to be really blown away, and i just... wasn't. It was all very good, especially the spicy scallop aguachile which was outstanding, but the rest of the dishes were good but not particularly memorable. I was a bit disappointed in my mezcal and charred pineapple cocktail but my husband really liked his. Glad we went, and maybe in the summer when there's more exciting produce we would have a different opinion but we were both just expecting something a little more.
Awesome food!
Excellent meal; every dish was well-executed. Novel takes without being fussy. It was very loud but we by chance had the corner booth. Great drinks as well.
Just got a one star. Classic, simple and homemade food. Small menu, but great selection. The freshly made tortilla is delicious!
Delicious. Outright tasty.
(Translated by Google) The best very rich corn  (Original) El mejor maíz muy rico

brought the bf here for his birthday and we both REALLY enjoyed our meal; our server was awesome (young lady with short blond hair) and place was cute as a button. we had been to oxomoco a few weeks before, and this place blew it out of the water - while both are different approaches to oaxacan, the creativity in the food here was on a different level (for both having a michelin star). do try the:  - farm salad - sepia tostada - yellowfin tostada - tacos campechano - mole rojo  i can’t wait to go back 😋.
Food is ?????  Drinks are the only reason for me to go back.

The hot spot in Bk, I was told & definitely not a disappointment. Okay, you have to wait, but that's the price you pay for dining at a restaurant recently acclaimed in a reputable newspaper. I did chuckle when the waiter of a Oaxacan restaurant told me they served quote-unquote "Mexican coke". Try the Taco Campechano - very tasty and well executed. The dessert, on the other hand, was a disappointment (hence the four-star review), so next time I know I save that space in my stomach for another appetizer.
You HAVE to go here.
The tacos, the cocktails, and the dessert all beg to be tasted with closed eyes... and then they go "Pow!". Awesome place!

Everyone here was super nice and generous. The ambiance was amazing and the perfect place to celebrate a birthday. I’m giving three stars for two important reasons.  1. Temperature. This place was freezing cold and was quite uncomfortable to sit in without shivering. Each time the door swung open you were met with winter brisk. There’s not currently a resolve since the only visible heater unit is just above the employees only section in the middle of the restaurant. So basically I ate with my winter jacket wrapped around me and several others did, too. Prob not the best place to go on a cold (under 40 degrees) winter day/night  2. Only two out of four dishes were applaudable. Those were the crab empanada (my favorite) and the mole short rib. The other two: Chorizo Memela and Octopus and Bacon tostada. Chorizo Memela’s texture was all mush. It needed crunch and we felt like an ingredient was missing. The Octopus and Bacon Tostada left a lot to be desired. It all just blended in together. There was no taste, which is surprising because BACON. Those two dishes just fell really short of the bar for a Michelin Star restaurant.
Seriously the best food.

Awesome food and excellent service!  I ordered Pork Memela, Oaxacan Beans, and a side of tortillas and enjoyed my meal at the bar.  The flavors were great, the Pork Memela had some heat but just enough so anyone could enjoy.
Get the tostada and the pork mole. Very good
Would give them 6 stars if I could! The food was great and they had awesome cocktails.

(Translated by Google) This is Mexico. Excellent atmosphere Cozy place and the food and cocktails are excellent.  (Original) Esto es México. Excelente ambiente. Lugar acogedor y la comida y cocktails son excelentes.
The food is strong albeit a bit pricey for what it is. For better or worse, the bar menu is very mezcal focused.
Amazing food. Only quibble is that the cocktail list isn’t very diverse if you’re not a fan of Mezcal (though I am).
The food was good, especially the mole, but it was slightly overpriced for the portions.
Food and drinks are amazing. Great atmosphere
Definitely get the frozen mezcal drink. The pulpo was a standout!

I would like to give this place a bit better rating, but the issue was value, not quality. Two of us had a drink (one non-alcoholic) and an appy and it was $75. The food was good, but the drinks not great. Hard to reckoned a place when you leave feeling you’ve really over paid.

Had high expectations but food was mediocre and service was awful. They started by not allowing us to seat outside even though they had tables that stayed unoccupied our whole meal. We waited ~20 min between plates and staff was very non-responsive.
Delicious & flavorful. They know how to cook pork. (Dessert was more of a souffle, though)
Margaritas made with mezcal and delicious Oaxacan food. So good!
Fabulous spot in Gowanus. Oxacan small plates paired with incredible cocktails. You'll feel like you just stepped into a Mexican cantina.
Great food and amazing cocktails.
Fantastic small plates and great service.  For something next to the Gowanus Canal it has no right being this nuanced and delicious. Great Mescal selection too.
Great brunch. Looks like dinner would be even better
Fantastic refined Mexican food in Brooklyn!

Chef does an incredible job with balance.  The food here tastes like you are eating at the best restaurant in Oaxaca instead of Gowanas.  If you haven't been, go.  If you live nearby, go often.  Don't forget to drink all the mezcal.
Very good cocktails and food

Seriously one of the best (Mexican) places in the city. Do not expect the traditional things (like guaca and chips), but promise you will not leave disappointed. Must try the tuna tostada and one of their mescal drinks 👌🏽
Simple yet complex flavors. Clear care and attention to each detail and ingredient.
chilled atmosphere and great food.
The yellowfin tostada is outstanding. Space tends to get pretty loud, backyard seating might be a better choice if the weather's nice.
Excellent food and service
The atmosphere was a low lit, but buzzy bar scene. The food was great, but I wish menu included full meals. Kind of like a tapas style bar if you’re into that, but it’ll get quickly expensive.
Great food cozy spot
Unbelievable brunch - try the chilaquiles and the agua fresca. I can't wait to go back for dinner.
Terrible service
its ok

Oaxacan flavors can be very layered/complex, and i found this interpretation to be exceptionally dense. Although they recommend sharing, plates are small and the total adds up quick. Our table thought it was very expensive and some left hungry. I was expecting something easier...the food was sort of...overwhelming, like, i can't eat more of this, even though I'm hungry. The vibe was relaxed, even if the food was intense. The back yard area looked pretty. Whereas i expected to want to return again and again, this is more of 'I need some time before i go back'. The most memorable: lengua and barbacoa tacos and chocolate dessert
Excellent! Everything was delicious!

Brooklyn's version of Cosme minus the swanky decor. The cocktail menu provides a number of creative drinks I had one with duck fat and sesame oil that was crazy delicious. Highlights on the food menu included the yellowfin tostada with acocado and citrus. I will definitely be heading back for both of those items!
Must try in New York! I loved the food, service, and drinks. Could not have been any better. I can't wait to go back🤤!
Amazing authentic Mexican food. Great atmosphere.
Mole was good, but those beef tongue tacos were on fire. Great server, and a lot of mezcal for my hipster tastes.

Claro is an Oaxacan style restaurant. Menu changes frequently and is seasonal. I had the octopus tostada, vegetable memela, mole pork cheek, and yellowfin tostada. All dishes were well planned,thought out and balanced. Prices are a reasonable for the quality of ingredients.
Go there for one of the best mole ever and stay for the fantastic cocktails! A must try.

4.17.18 - The staff is great and the space is design with interesting accents and prints on the wall. The crowd can get a little loud and it'll fill up fast after 5:30 PM.  The food is generally good, but nothing super enough to write home. The drinks definitely shine especially the drink that's based around rendered duck fat and sesame; it's a Mezcal duck fat washed milk punch with amaro and sesame.  I think the prices are a little bit on the higher side, but there was a good amount of preparation in each dish, so it's understandable. Does it wow the palate or shine in any particular way? No, but it's still satisfying.
Wonderful Oaxacan cuisine. Lots of fun.
The food was fine. Nothing special, flavors were a bit muddled. Cocktails were also just mediocre. The short rib molé was amazing. Prices were extravagant.

Do you want a great dining experience with superb service and food at a decent price? Check Claro out. Great service, help with menu, dietary restrictions, etc. Each interaction was personal, I felt like I was being cared for. The food was fantastic, diverse flavors on offer: spring salad was fresh and pea leaves were sweet (the dressing is robust, borderline overpowering but didn’t quite get there), yellow fin tostada was balanced - good quality fish with creamy avocado and sweet tortilla, tacos had similar flavor profile (our ordering) - pulpo was good texture (enough bite, but not rubbery) and flavor, duck chile relleno in mole sauce was well executed - rich flavors in and out. And oh my lord, the chocolate dessert is the best - I don’t eat sweets much and I loved this.
The Tastiest Tuesday Tacos
The avocado & beet tostada and yellowfin tuna tostada are two of my favorite things I've eaten recently.
One of my favorite high end Mexican places in all of NYC! Cocktails amazing too
Able to accommodate us as a walk in on a busy Saturday night, good experience, great tortilla
Food is amazing! I loved the tuna taco and octopus. Great place for date night or hanging out with the girls. The staff is super nice too!
Food was excellent, small portions.  A bit too loud for me.
Incredible food and drinks!  I'd recommend sharing 4 plates. The turkey tikka is a must have.  Can't wait to go back!
The food is great very unique and tasty. A great experience for a night. I loved it.
Delicious! Amazing service, incredible food and cocktails.

Delicious food. Great service, awesome vibe, great selection of cocktails and mezcal. Small plates which is perfect to try a lot of different options and it makes the diner more fun. The only thing I would say is that some dishes are spicy and some people cant handle the heat, so maybe you should show it on the menu. Other than that, nothing but perfection. An amazing experience and we will be back for more very soon.

Enjoyable food. Server said shareable .im not sure  that the dishes were that shareable .hats off to the little ladies in the back knocking out the authenticity of the dishes. Tortialls made to order ,really add to the quality of the dishes. I felt that the Staff wasnt   the friendly bunch .certainly not as nice as the group before them.
Amazing food and drink.  Lovely staff.
Amazing food. Authentic Oaxacan cusine. Great Mezcal Cocktails.
All around excellent meal. Mezcal list is no joke too.
Good cocktails and innovative menu.

Fantastic new spot in Gowanus - cozy vibe, great service and consistently   amazing Oaxacan food  that made me want to lick my plate clean.  No joke.  Salmon aguachile, pulpo tostada, butternut squash mole, shrimp tacos all amazing.
AMAZING mole!!! Best I've ever had.

Had a reservation. Arrived 40 minutes early. We were seated 45 minutes after our reservation. Throwing out a star because the food was decent.
The food was absolutely delicious! Try the octopus with bacon— you won’t be disappointed. Dishes are easy to share and the portions are reasonable. This is a perfect place to bring a date.

There is a lot of hype about this place, and understandably so given that Freeks Mill is spot on for me. Claro was good, but the portions are small and a bit salty for my taste. We had the Lobster Tostada, Shrimp Aguachile, Tetela, Salmon Ceviche and Wild Mushroom Quesadilla. My friend and I dont have huge appetites but we ordered five dishes and could have had another. The Mezcal drinks on the other hand were delicious, I would go back just for one of those.
Very good upscale Mexican

An authentic yet Brooklyn Oaxacan seasonal restaurant. Came in on a Friday night and you need a reservation. The backyard was open with heaters but we opted for the bar indoors. The steak tlayuda was the best item. Steak cooked perfect! Food comes out when it’s ready. Will definitely be back and try other homemade tortilla items.

Our dinner was FANTASTIC. Our cocktails were perfectly balanced; waiter was attentive and food was to die for. Would recommend sitting in the backyard where you can see the cooks working over the open fire.
The pairing of smokey sulties of the mezcal cocktails with the wood fired dishes really compliments each other well. Defintely a wonderful dinning experience to be had.
This place is amazing. Authentic Oaxacan food, the tortillas are to die for. Definitely make the trip to Gowanus to try this place!

Staff is great, location is not and this claims to be a Mexican restaurant but it lacks all the Mexican ingredients: first of all no avocado, second tortillas are beyond mediocre and third when I asked for salsas they brought Valentina, I'm Mexican so I know what I'm talking about if you want Mexican food don't go here.
